cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the formalism for investigating the semantics of game logic, which is related to logic and artificial intelligence (cs.LO, cs.AI). The paper also discusses algebraic properties of stochastic effectivity functions, which is related to game theory (cs.GT), and stochastic relations, morphisms, and congruences, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and systems and control (cs.SI).
